race.comment: INCOGNITO (6) did enough in a trial on the Kensington track on 22 September to suggest he is ready for this. From the stable of last year's Slipper winner and is by a Slipper winner. Should be at decent each-way odds and is a worthwhile bet on that basis. PARADOXIUM (7) was easily accounted for by I'M YA HUCKLEBERRY in their Kensington trial. Draws the fence and should have a bit saved up the sleeve for race day. EVICTION NOTICE (2) heads a strong Waterhouse/Bott contingent. Smashed his rivals and the clock in his trial win, running virtually the same time as today's rival I'M YA HUCKLEBERRY. Sure to meet with strong market support. Stablemate I'M YA HUCKLEBERRY (4) disposed of many of today's field in his trial win on 22 September. A wide gate is the only knock. ARTANEOUS (1) went well in his trial and is worth monitoring for market support.
